=Description=

De Seta:

"The Biomimicry Index is a conceptual indicator for assessing how well human organizations respect the principles of living systems.

It allows for the evaluation of what I consider to be the five fundamental principles of life: cellular structure, the capacity for growth and complexification, metabolism, homeostasis, and reproducibility.

It is also an assessment tool that enables the quick identification of obstacles to an organization's development, as well as the risks to the health of social bodies."

(https://de-seta.com/mes-creations)


